The paper deals with the problem of non-rigid structure-from-motion, which is a topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes a new method for solving this problem using low-rank decomposition, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The method involves back-projection of vectors into 3D space, which is a topic in computer graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM). Therefore, these four categories are the most likely. Other possible categories could include cs.RO (robotics) or cs.SI (signal processing), but they are less likely given the focus of the paper.
